WEBVTT

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:08.800
<v Teacher>We mentioned that with future context we can talk about the future using the present.

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:12.240
<v Teacher>For example, we had <i>tomorrow</i> which was:

00:00:13.560 --> 00:00:14.440
<v Student><b>Mañana.</b>

00:00:14.440 --> 00:00:15.720
<v Teacher><b>Mañana. </b>Good.

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:21.480
<v Teacher>We had <i>later</i>, or <i>more late</i>, which was: <b>Más tarde.</b>

00:00:21.640 --> 00:00:23.400
<v Student><b>Más tarde.</b>

00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:26.760
<v Teacher><b>Más tarde.</b> We had <i>tonight</i>, or <i>this night</i>:

00:00:27.480 --> 00:00:28.680
<v Student><b>Esta noche.</b>

00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:30.040
<v Teacher>Esta noche.

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:30.760
<v Teacher>Good.

00:00:30.760 --> 00:00:33.160
<v Teacher>Another one is <b>pronto</b>.

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:33.800
<v Teacher><b>pronto</b>

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:36.280
<v Teacher>What do you think <b>pronto</b> means?

00:00:37.260 --> 00:00:38.300
<v Student><i>Now.</i>

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:40.300
<v Teacher><b>Ahora</b> was <i>now</i>, no?

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:41.660
<v Student><i>Soon</i>?

00:00:41.660 --> 00:00:42.300
<v Teacher><i>Soon</i>. Yeah.

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:47.579
<v Teacher>You hear in English sometimes <i>get here pronto</i>. It's <i>get here soon</i>.

00:00:47.579 --> 00:00:51.100
<v Teacher>So <b>pronto</b> is also future context.

00:00:51.180 --> 00:00:55.660
<v Teacher>What was the verb <i>to see</i>, or <i>to view</i>?

00:00:55.660 --> 00:00:56.700
<v Student><b>Ver.</b>

00:00:56.700 --> 00:00:59.340
<v Teacher><i>He sees</i>:

00:00:59.340 --> 00:00:59.820
<v Student><b>Ve.</b>

00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:00.620
<v Teacher>Good.

00:01:00.620 --> 00:01:01.100
<v Teacher><i>They</i>:

00:01:01.100 --> 00:01:02.700
<v Student><b>Ven.</b>

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:04.780
<v Teacher><i>You</i> (informal):

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:05.500
<v Student><b>Ves.</b>

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:06.500
<v Teacher><i>We</i>:

00:01:09.939 --> 00:01:10.740
<v Student><b>Vemos.</b>

00:01:10.740 --> 00:01:11.380
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:21.939
<v Teacher>The <i>I</i> version is a tiny bit irregular, it's <b>veo</b>. So you have <i>v-e-o</i>. So it's not <b>vo</b> as it should be, or /<i>bo</i>/. It was too short; it became <b>veo</b>.

00:01:21.939 --> 00:01:22.659
<v Student><b>Veo.</b>

00:01:22.659 --> 00:01:30.120
<v Teacher><i>V-e-o.</i> /<i>beo</i>/ or /<i>veo</i>/. How would you say: <i>I'm seeing her later</i>?

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:40.200
<v Teacher>That means <i>I see she later</i>.

00:01:41.860 --> 00:01:43.460
<v Student>It's not <b>la</b>?

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:44.100
<v Teacher>It is.

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:45.620
<v Student>Oh so it's <b>la veo</b>.

00:01:45.620 --> 00:01:47.140
<v Teacher><b>La veo.</b> Good.

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:50.340
<v Student><b>La veo más tarde.</b>

00:01:50.340 --> 00:01:52.020
<v Teacher><b>La veo más tarde.</b>

00:01:52.260 --> 00:01:55.460
<v Teacher><i>I'm seeing her tonight</i>:

00:01:55.460 --> 00:01:56.420
<v Student><b>La veo esta noche.</b>

00:01:56.420 --> 00:01:58.580
<v Teacher>Good. <b>La veo esta noche.</b>

00:01:58.580 --> 00:02:03.460
<v Teacher><i>We are seeing her soon</i>. <i>We are seeing her soon</i>:

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:09.280
<v Student><b>La venemos pronto.</b>

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:10.560
<v Teacher>What is: <i>to see</i>?

00:02:10.560 --> 00:02:12.480
<v Student>Sorry it should be <b>vemos</b>?

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:15.640
<v Teacher>Yes. So no guessing.

00:02:15.640 --> 00:02:18.520
<v Teacher>No guessing at all. It's the only rule.

00:02:18.520 --> 00:02:20.760
<v Student><b>La vemos pronto.</b>

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:21.400
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:21.740 --> 00:02:23.340
<v Teacher><b>La vemos pronto.</b>

00:02:23.340 --> 00:02:30.380
<v Teacher>What if we say <i>we're seeing, we will see, them soon</i> but with this <i>them</i> we mean a female group? <i>We're seeing them soon</i>:

00:02:33.480 --> 00:02:35.560
<v Student><b>Las vemos pronto.</b>

00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:36.200
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:38.680
<v Teacher><b>Las vemos pronto.</b>

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:42.760
<v Teacher><i>He is seeing them soon.</i> And this <i>them,</i> they are still females. <i>He is seeing them soon:</i>

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:44.760
<v Student><b>Las ve pronto.</b>

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:49.020
<v Teacher>Good. And <i>you</i> (informal):

00:02:49.020 --> 00:02:51.820
<v Student><b>La ves pronto.</b>

00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:55.820
<v Teacher><i>Them</i> soon. <i>You're seeing them</i>:

00:02:55.820 --> 00:02:58.140
<v Student><b>Las ves pronto.</b>

00:02:58.140 --> 00:02:58.540
<v Teacher>Good.

00:02:58.540 --> 00:03:03.900
<v Teacher>I'll make it a question: <i>are you seeing them soon?</i> The female <i>them</i>.

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:05.580
<v Student><b>¿Las ves pronto?</b>

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:07.180
<v Teacher><b>¿Las ves pronto?</b>

00:03:07.180 --> 00:03:09.420
<v Teacher><i>Aren't you seeing them soon?</i>:

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:12.500
<v Student><b>¿No las ves pronto?</b>

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:15.000
<v Teacher><b>¿No las ves pronto?</b>

00:03:15.000 --> 00:03:17.540
<v Teacher><i>Why aren't you seeing them soon?</i>:

00:03:17.540 --> 00:03:19.700
<v Student><b>¿Por qué no las ves pronto?</b>

00:03:19.700 --> 00:03:20.740
<v Teacher>Good. <b>¿Por qué no las ves pronto?</b> Very good.

00:03:20.540 --> 00:03:31.100
<v Teacher>So we saw that with future context, we don't need the future. If we don't have future context, we can still use the present to talk about the future using this <i>I go</i> or <i>I'm going</i>, which is present, but we can use it to talk about the future in Spanish as we do in English.

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:42.060
<v Teacher><i>I'm going to see her</i>, and you're talking about the future. <i>We're going to see her</i>. So let's practice that - how would you say: <i>we're going to see her</i>?

00:03:42.060 --> 00:03:47.900
<v Student><b>Vamos a verla.</b>

00:03:47.900 --> 00:04:04.900
<v Teacher><i>Are you going to see him soon?</i> Speaking informally. <i>Are you going to see him soon?</i> So you can't work with <b>ir</b>, which is <i>to go</i>. You should probably work with <b>vamos</b> and work backwards.

00:04:06.319 --> 00:04:08.400
<v Student><b>Vas. ¿Vas a verlo pronto?</b>

00:04:08.400 --> 00:04:11.920
<v Teacher>Good. <b>¿Vas a verlo pronto?</b>

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:22.280
<v Teacher>The word for <i>us</i> is <b>nos</b>. <b>Nos.</b> So how would you say <i>are you going to see us soon?</i> <i>Are you going to see us soon?</i> And we're still speaking informally.

00:04:26.900 --> 00:04:31.140
<v Student><b>¿Vas a vernos pronto?</b>

00:04:31.140 --> 00:04:32.180
<v Teacher>Very good.

00:04:32.180 --> 00:04:35.860
<v Teacher><b>¿Vas a vernos pronto?</b> Where else could that <b>nos</b> go?

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:38.480
<v Student>At the beginning.

00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:41.360
<v Teacher>Before the changed verb.

00:04:41.360 --> 00:04:44.720
<v Student><b>¿Nos vas a ver pronto?</b>

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:52.180
<v Teacher>Very good. <b>¿Nos vas a ver pronto?</b> <i>Aren't you going to see us soon?</i>

00:04:52.500 --> 00:04:56.759
<v Student><b>¿No vas a ver pronto- nos pronto?</b>

00:04:57.000 --> 00:05:01.800
<v Teacher>Good. <b>¿No vas a vernos pronto?</b> Or <b>¿No nos vas a ver pronto?</b> Either way.

00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:04.280
<v Teacher><i>Why aren't you going to see us soon?</i>

00:05:04.660 --> 00:05:08.580
<v Student><b>¿Por qué no vas a vernos pronto?</b>

00:05:08.580 --> 00:05:17.199
<v Teacher>Good. So we've seen that we can use the present to talk about the future using "going to", or also using future context.

00:05:17.199 --> 00:05:26.319
<v Teacher>A word like <i>tomorrow</i>, <i>next week</i>; <i>next week</i> is "the week that comes". And <i>the week</i> is <b>la semana</b>. <b>La semana.</b>

00:05:26.319 --> 00:05:32.560
<v Teacher>How would you say <i>the week that comes</i>? So what is the word for <i>that</i>, which is the same as <i>what</i>?

00:05:33.759 --> 00:05:37.199
<v Student><b>Que.</b>

00:05:37.199 --> 00:05:42.260
<v Teacher><b>Que. La semana que</b>, <i>the week that, the week which, comes</i>. And here we mean <i>the week comes</i>. So it's <i>it comes</i>. So what is: <i>it comes</i>?

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:44.980
<v Student><b>Vene. Viene.</b>

00:05:44.980 --> 00:05:47.060
<v Teacher>Good.

00:05:47.060 --> 00:05:52.420
<v Teacher>So next week is <b>la semana que viene</b>. <i>The week that comes</i>. <b>La semana que viene.</b>

00:05:52.500 --> 00:06:01.780
<v Teacher>So you could say <i>let's speak</i>, and to say <i>let's speak</i> we know from <b>vamos</b> you can just use the "we" form. So <i>to speak</i> is:

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:04.360
<v Student><b>Hablar.</b>

00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.920
<v Teacher><b>Hablar.</b> <i>We speak</i>:

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:07.960
<v Student><b>Hablamos.</b>

00:06:07.960 --> 00:06:11.880
<v Teacher><i>Let's speak next week</i>. <i>Let's speak the week that comes.</i>

00:06:11.880 --> 00:06:16.840
<v Student><b>Hablamos la semana que</b>- And now I've forgotten <i>come</i>.

00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:23.680
<v Teacher>It's okay. Okay. If we forgot it, we need to find it again. That's not any problem.

00:06:23.680 --> 00:06:28.720
<v Teacher>Every time we do find it, we strengthen that process. And that's what we need,

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:31.040
<v Teacher>not to remember the word.

00:06:30.440 --> 00:06:32.200
<v Teacher>The process we need to strengthen.

00:06:32.200 --> 00:06:37.160
<v Teacher>I want you to know how to find <i>to come</i> and then to go from there. <i>It comes</i>.

00:06:37.160 --> 00:06:39.000
<v Teacher>Take your time to find <i>it comes</i>.

00:06:40.300 --> 00:06:41.100
<v Student><b>Vene.</b>

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:43.820
<v Teacher>It would be <b>vene</b> but: <b>Viene.</b>

00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:46.620
<v Teacher><i>Let's speak the coming week</i>:

00:06:46.620 --> 00:06:49.320
<v Student><b>Hablamos que</b>-

00:06:49.320 --> 00:06:53.240
<v Teacher>At the moment you have the whole sentence in your mind and you want to translate it.

00:06:53.240 --> 00:06:56.040
<v Teacher>Now this process works when you're memorizing.

00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:57.400
<v Teacher>But we're not memorizing.

00:06:57.400 --> 00:06:58.600
<v Teacher>We're doing something else;

00:06:58.600 --> 00:06:59.320
<v Teacher>we're building.

00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:00.360
<v Teacher>So we must

00:07:00.520 --> 00:07:05.560
<v Teacher>reduce it down to the smallest piece we could possibly think about,

00:07:05.560 --> 00:07:08.280
<v Teacher>think about that piece, get it out, and then forget it.

00:07:08.280 --> 00:07:11.880
<v Teacher>So the first bit is <i>we speak/let's speak</i>:

00:07:11.880 --> 00:07:14.120
<v Student><b>Hablamos.</b>

00:07:14.120 --> 00:07:16.000
<v Teacher><i>The week</i>:

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:18.000
<v Student><b>La semana.</b>

00:07:18.000 --> 00:07:19.479
<v Teacher><i>Which</i>, or <i>that</i>, <i>comes</i>.

00:07:20.720 --> 00:07:22.000
<v Student><b>Que vene- viene.</b>

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.960
<v Teacher><b>Viene.</b> Good.

00:07:24.960 --> 00:07:27.440
<v Teacher><b>Hablamos la semana que viene.</b>

00:07:27.440 --> 00:07:30.080
<v Teacher>What was to see, or to view?

00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:31.280
<v Student><b>Ver.</b>

00:07:31.280 --> 00:07:31.760
<v Teacher>Ver.

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.920
<v Teacher>What is we see?

00:07:33.920 --> 00:07:34.800
<v Student><b>Vemos.</b>

00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:35.360
<v Teacher>Vemos.

00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:37.840
<v Teacher>If you want to say we see each other,

00:07:38.240 --> 00:07:40.400
<v Teacher>you say <i>we see us</i>.

00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:45.680
<v Teacher><b>Nos</b> can mean <i>us</i>, <i>ourselves, each </i> <i>other</i>, it can mean all of that.

00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:46.320
<v Teacher><b>Nos</b>.

00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:49.040
<v Teacher>So how do you say: <i>we see ourselves</i>?

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:52.600
<v Student><b>Nos vemos.</b>

00:07:52.600 --> 00:07:53.560
<v Teacher>Nos vemos.

00:07:53.560 --> 00:07:56.120
<v Teacher>This is a way of saying goodbye in Spanish.

00:07:56.120 --> 00:07:57.160
<v Teacher><b>Nos vemos</b>,

00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:58.280
<v Teacher><i>we see each other</i>.

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:01.720
<v Teacher>Now the future context here is the fact that you're saying goodbye.

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:06.320
<v Teacher>But we're using present because we know when we say <b>nos vemos</b> we don't mean we're seeing each other right now,

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:08.080
<v Teacher>we mean <i>we will </i> <i>see each other again</i>.

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:13.680
<v Teacher>We're not even mentioning that future context, but it's working. It's allowing us to use the present there.

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:14.720
<v Teacher>Nos vemos,

00:08:14.940 --> 00:08:15.820
<v Teacher>ciao.

00:08:15.820 --> 00:08:19.020
<v Teacher>Or you might want to say, <i>we will see each other next </i> <i>week</i>.

00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:19.980
<v Teacher>How would you say that?

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:22.380
<v Teacher>So piece by piece. <i>We see each other.</i>

00:08:22.380 --> 00:08:24.860
<v Teacher>I want all of your mental energy on that, and not

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:28.760
<v Teacher>thinking yet about <i>next week</i>, how you will say that.

00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:36.599
<v Teacher>What you're worried about right now in this moment is how you're going to say <i>we see ourselves</i>. And even before that, just <i>we see:</i>

00:08:37.940 --> 00:08:41.620
<v Student>So it's <b>vemos</b>. And it's <b>nos vemos</b>.

00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:42.339
<v Teacher>Good.

00:08:42.339 --> 00:08:44.180
<v Teacher><i>The week that comes</i>.

00:08:44.180 --> 00:08:45.459
<v Teacher>So <i>the week</i>:

00:08:46.399 --> 00:08:49.839
<v Student><b>La semana que viene.</b>

00:08:49.839 --> 00:08:50.639
<v Teacher>Good.

00:08:50.639 --> 00:08:52.560
<v Teacher><b>Nos vemos la semana que viene.</b>

00:08:52.639 --> 00:08:55.120
<v Teacher>So you see it's not important to remember <b>viene</b>.

00:08:55.120 --> 00:08:56.399
<v Teacher>We don't want to remember <b>viene</b>,

00:08:56.399 --> 00:08:57.120
<v Teacher>this is useless.

00:08:57.120 --> 00:09:00.160
<v Teacher>In fact, if we memorize <b>viene</b>, we're just going to be

00:09:00.259 --> 00:09:01.940
<v Teacher>glazing over the problem.

00:09:02.420 --> 00:09:06.819
<v Teacher>What we want to internalize is the process of “how do I find this".

00:09:06.819 --> 00:09:12.980
<v Teacher>So, we've seen that we can use the present to talk about the future

00:09:13.520 --> 00:09:20.960
<v Teacher>using either <b>ir</b><b>a</b>: <i>to go to</i>; <b>voy a, </b> <b>vamos a, va a</b>; or using some future context.
